Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19277&quot; title=&quot;add man pages for functions in liblustreapi_fid.c&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19277&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-19277&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; doc: add man pages for llapi_* functions&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 3d51cda262a74c1e1cea94ea4643a3e2e5949e74&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="469596" author="adilger" created="Sun, 31 Aug 2025 16:38:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think it is necessary to provide all of the detail in llapi_fid2path(). The llapi_fid_parse() behavior should be documented in that man page, and then write in the  llapi_fid2path() man page that it calls llapi_fid_parse() to parse the fid string, it is enough to write something like &quot;-EINVAL returned if argument is missing or empty&quot;, &quot;-ERANGE returned if field is too large&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="469595" author="JIRAUSER19447" created="Sun, 31 Aug 2025 09:42:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Function &lt;tt&gt;llapi_fid2path()&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;returns &lt;tt&gt;-EINVAL&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;-ERANGE&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;-EINVAL&lt;/tt&gt; is returned in case:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Path give is null pointer or an empty string.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While parsing &lt;tt&gt;fidstr&lt;/tt&gt; using &lt;tt&gt;llapi_fid_parse()&lt;/tt&gt;, any of the 3 FID fields are zero or &lt;tt&gt;strtoull()&lt;/tt&gt; return &lt;tt&gt;EINVAL&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;-ERANGE&lt;/tt&gt; is returned in case:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While parsing &lt;tt&gt;fidstr&lt;/tt&gt; using &lt;tt&gt;llapi_fid_parse()&lt;/tt&gt;, any of the 3 FID fields are out of range in positive direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;-EINVAL&lt;/tt&gt; second point and &lt;tt&gt;-ERANGE&lt;/tt&gt;, both are returned by &lt;tt&gt;llapi_fid_parse()&lt;/tt&gt; which was called inside &lt;tt&gt;llapi_fid2path()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have 2 ways I can include this info in man page:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Explain the above points in the same detail.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Document them as wrong syntax for FID string.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
